\section*{Problem Statement}

Two parallel bars of different materials with linear coefficients of expansion $\alpha_1$ and $\alpha_2$, respectively, are riveted together at a distance $d$ apart. An increase in temperature $\Delta T$ will cause them to bend into circular arcs with a common center, subtending an angle $\theta$ at the center (see Fig.~\ref{fig:bimetal_strip}). Find the mean radius of curvature.

