The time \( t \) required to transfer the heat \( Q \) is:
\[
t = \frac{Q}{\dot{Q}} = \frac{16736}{141.37} \approx 118.4 \, \si{\second}
\]

Thus, it will take approximately \SI{118.4}{\second} to melt \SI{50}{\gram} of ice.

